results.content: Cristiano Ronaldo is a Portuguese professional footballer who plays as a forward "Forward (association football)") for and captains "Captain (association football)") both Saudi Pro League club Al-Nassr and the Portugal national team. On 29 September 2002, Ronaldo made his debut in the Primeira Liga, playing for Sporting CP's first team against Braga, and on 7 October, he scored two goals against Moreirense in their 3–0 win. Ronaldo ended his first season in English football by scoring the opening goal in United's 3–0 win over Millwall in the 2004 FA Cup Final, earning his first trophy. Ronaldo won his second trophy in English football, the Football League Cup, after scoring the third goal in United's 4–0 final win over Wigan Athletic.
